{"name":"Macro Instructions","content":"<p>Monk's Active Tiles will pass in additional data to macros.</p>\n<p>By accessing arguments[0] you can gain reference to the following:</p>\n<p>actor: This references the current Actor that triggered the Tile.</p>\n<p>args: an array of arguments passed into the macro via Active Tiles.  Each argument will be split on spaces, and if you do not want a string to be split, then you'll need to wrap it in double quotes.</p>\n<p>canvas: references the current canvas,</p>\n<p>method: it the method that triggered the Tile.  Enter, Exit, Movement, and Click</p>\n<p>scene: references the applicable scene</p>\n<p>tile: is the tile that was triggered.</p>\n<p>token: references the token that triggered the tile</p>\n<p>tokens: references the original set of tokens involved </p>\n<p>user: the user that triggered the tile</p>\n<p>value: the set of values returned by the previous action</p>\n<p>values: a running set of values of all the previous actions</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Returning an object with various properties will change how Active Tiles continues to process {continue, tokens, goto, location, activate, items, actors}</p>\n<p>if continue is set to false, then Active TIles will stop and further actions.</p>\n<p>if tokens is set to an array of TokenDocuments, these tokens will be used as the current set of tokens for the remaining actions.</p>\n<p>goto will find an achor with that name and start actions after that point.</p>\n<p>location can be used to set the location of teleport and other actions that use a location.</p>\n<p>activate can be used by the Activate action to determine what value to use.</p>\n<p>items can be used by the Add Item action</p>\n<p>actors can be used by the Create Actor action.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":null,"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"NoP0yFyEU0MJHD4O":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.6Sa0kMpUByrdycZR"}},"_id":"tP3Rv3nxqUxz2lMF"}
